    <h2><span class="section-num">7</span> Motion Principles</h2>
    <div class="motion-grid">
      <div class="motion-card">
        <h4>Gathering Phase</h4>
        <p>Objects slowly float/drift toward center — anticipation. Easing: <code>ease-in</code>. Slow start, accelerating.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="motion-card">
        <h4>Burst Phase</h4>
        <p>Sudden acceleration — everything snaps into place at lightspeed. <code>cubic-bezier(0.25, 0, 0, 1)</code></p>
      </div>
      <div class="motion-card">
        <h4>The Light Sweep ✦</h4>
        <p>Signature move: warm-white beam travels horizontally across frame at transformation completion. This IS the "lightspeed" moment.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="motion-card">
        <h4>Liquid Idle State</h4>
        <p>Even in the "after" state, liquid gently undulates. Pools → ripples (2–3 cycles) → calms. Always alive. <code>ease-in-out</code> loop.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

