  <section>
    <h2><span class="section-num" style="background:#0A1E3D;">☾</span> Dark Mode Direction</h2>

    <p>Dark mode is a valid and powerful brand direction for LightSpeed VT. It creates contrast, drama, and makes the glass + liquid elements glow with maximum impact. Use it for:</p>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Context</th><th>Dark Mode Treatment</th></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Hero banners</strong></td><td>Deep midnight (#0A1E3D) or near-black (#05080F) — glass panel glows as focal point</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Sales presentations</strong></td><td>Dark background slides where the glass UI "emerges from darkness"</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Social media</strong></td><td>High contrast: dark bg + electric blue glass edge + white text</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Video intros</strong></td><td>Open on black, light sweep reveals glass panel and LightSpeed VT logo</td></tr>
    </table>

    <h3 style="margin-top:20px;">Dark Mode Color Adjustments</h3>
    <div class="css-block" style="margin-top:8px;">
      <span class="css-prop">background:</span> <span class="css-val">#050D1A to #0A1E3D</span>; <span style="color:#666;">/* deep midnight */</span><br>
      <span class="css-prop">glass-tint:</span> <span class="css-val">rgba(10, 40, 100, 0.4)</span>; <span style="color:#666;">/* deeper blue tint */</span><br>
      <span class="css-prop">glass-border:</span> <span class="css-val">rgba(77, 166, 255, 0.7)</span>; <span style="color:#666;">/* brighter edge glow */</span><br>
      <span class="css-prop">glass-shadow:</span> <span class="css-val">0 0 40px rgba(43, 127, 232, 0.4)</span>; <span style="color:#666;">/* outer glow */</span><br>
      <span class="css-prop">liquid-brightness:</span> <span class="css-val">+30%</span>; <span style="color:#666;">/* more saturated in dark */</span><br>
      <span class="css-prop">text:</span> <span class="css-val">#E8F4FF</span>; <span style="color:#666;">/* ice white */</span>
    </div>

    <p style="margin-top:12px;"><strong>Key rule for dark mode:</strong> The liquid becomes more luminous — it's now the primary light source in the scene. The glass glows from within like a lit panel. The wood base goes charcoal or disappears into shadow.</p>
